# ~/.claude/CLAUDE.md — UnsafeContext personal baseline

# Copy this file's contents to ~/.claude/CLAUDE.md. Claude Code loads it in EVERY
# session, on any project. Keep it engine/language-agnostic — stack-specific rules
# belong in each project's own CLAUDE.md (a project rule overrides this on conflict).

## Working principles (all projects)

- Name the archetype/responsibility of a thing before building it; one responsibility per unit.
- No hidden global state: avoid singletons and service locators; prefer explicit, injected dependencies.
- Fail loud, not silent: surface broken assumptions with logged errors; never swallow exceptions; do not return default/null/0 on an error path without logging.
- Do not hand-edit fragile generated or binary files; use the proper tool or generate a script.
- Surface conflicts: if a request conflicts with a project rule, say so instead of silently violating it.

## Interaction style

- Concise, peer-level. Portuguese with English technical terms. No hand-holding on basics.

## Stack-specific rules

- Live in each project's CLAUDE.md (Unity projects import csharp.md + unity-architecture.md; a Flutter project would import its own). This file stays neutral.
